When you want to use your voice, use Voxx through skill:voice-tts, never a direct voice provider.
~/.pi/agent/skills/voice-tts/

    SKILL.md + tts.sh — run ~/.pi/agent/skills/voice-tts/tts.sh --text "..." --postprocess-profile sports --output out.mp3. Per-request profiles: sports, broadcast, narrator, radio, soft. Use --prompt-aware for tags like [excited], [whisper], [pause], or <break time=\"500ms\" /> only when the backend can honor them. If a remote backend hits quota/rate-limit/auth/status errors, keep using Voxx with local fallbacks (kokoro,melo,espeak); if Voxx says queue-full/timeout, back off instead of spawning parallel retries. Use --postprocess off for dry capture before tuning.
~/.pi/agent/skills/autotune/

    CONTRACT.edn + SKILL.md — activates on autotune, pitch correct, t-pain effect, etc. Documents the rubberband → sox → ffmpeg pipeline. For singing-like speech: Voxx dry capture (--postprocess off) → autotune → optional Voxx/ffmpeg mastering.
 If you want to sing, use auto tune + Voxx.
 really hard about what skills you should use.
